Network Design

Situation:
Telus.com has acquired googlecloud as client, hiring 2500 agents. Design a subnet with 2500 users and implement

Method:
  Given: 2500 nodes 
  Use CSI:
    Convert: 2500 network bits = 12 bits
    Subtract: /32 - /12 = /20 (3rd octet, 16i)
    Insert in 3rd octer 16

    Network: 10.0.16.0/20
      1st usable address: 10.0.16.1/20
      broadcast id: 10.0.31.255

   given: 4500
     4500 = 13 bits
     32 -13 = /19 (3rd, 32i)

  network: 10.0.32.0/19
    1st ip: 10.0.32.1
    broadcast: 10.0.63.255


/*****************************/

given: 850
  850 = 10 bits
  32 - 10 = 22 (3rd octet, 4i)
  10.0.4.0 /22
  10.0.4.1
  10.0.7.255
  10.0.8.0 /22


/**************************/
  given: 50
    10.0.0.64 /26
    10.0.0.65
    10.0.0.127
    10.0.0.128 /26


/***********************************************************/


if network is asked, use

C: convert 
A: add
I: insert

ex. Subnet for 70 offices using the available ip address space of 172.16.0.0/16. Give the subnet for the 3rd office
C: 70 offices = 7 bits [2,4,8,16,32,64,_128_] (ask "where does the number of offices found?. then get the highest bit

16 + 7 = /23 
A: (3rd octed, 2i)
I: 172.16.0.0/23, 172.16.2.0/23, 172.16.4.0/23, 172.0.6.0/23, 172.0.8.0/23 

TemPlate_CoreSW:
@D1Code

config t
vlan 25
 name GOOGLECLOUD.COM
 exit
Int vlan 25
 no shut
 ip add 10.0.32.1 255.255.224.0
ip dhcp excluded-add 10.0.32.1 10.0.32.100
ip dhcp pool GOOGLECLOUD.COM
 network 10.0.32.0 255.255.224.0
 default-router 10.0.32.1
 domain-name GOOGLECLOUD.COM
 dns-server 10.82.1.10
 option 150 ip 10.82.100.8
 end


@A1Access
conf t
int e0/0
  swi access vlan 25
  do sh ip dhcp binding
end

@P1
conf t
int e0/0
no shut
ip add dhcp
end



